title: SDSU Big Data Hackathon
description: Our team won second place in the 2024 Big Data Hackathon, sponsored by Sharp HealthCare, whose theme was “Enhancing Healthcare’s Digital Front Door”. We designed a working app prototype which aimed to build healthy habits in children from marginalized communities which could be integrated into the existing Sharp HealthCare app.

title: Meteorite fall analysis
description: Analyzed 1,000 meteorite landings using Python to assess meteorite mass and landing area distribution.

title: UCSD Synthesis 1 Project
description: Used a combination of a sentiment analysis algorithm and aid from native speakers to determine the change in tone that occurs when a sentence is translated using computer translation technology.

title: Data Analysis of Taylor Swift’s Discography
description: Analyzed trends using 20+ audio features provided by Spotify to build interactive search and song recommendation tools, such as a tool to determine track similarity.
